Description: Blazing fast terminal file manager written in Rust
 Yazi is a terminal file manager written in Rust, based on non-blocking
 async I/O. It aims to provide an efficient, user-friendly, and customizable
 file management experience.
 .
 Key features:
  - Full asynchronous support powered by the Tokio runtime
  - Built-in image preview (Kitty, iTerm2, Sixel, WezTerm, and more)
  - Syntax highlighting for source code files
  - Lua 5.5 plugin system for UI and functional customization
  - Virtual filesystem supporting remote files via SFTP
  - Integration with ripgrep, fd, fzf, and zoxide
  - Vim-like keybindings, multi-tab support, cross-directory selection
  - Bulk rename, archive extraction, and Git integration
